
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [strings.replace] slot to replace all occurrences of double spaces ("  ") in the value of the [strings.replace] node with a single space (" "). The [strings.replace] slot takes two arguments: the first argument specifies the substring to be replaced, and the second argument specifies the replacement substring. In this case, it effectively normalizes spaces in a string by converting any double spaces into single spaces.
strings.replace:x:@strings.replace
   .:"  "
   .:" "
